><p>That's takeaway number one. Define the purpose of your trip to guide yo=
ur spending. Why is this such an important first step when traveling on a b=
udget? Because to clearly curtail your spending, you need to get clear on w=
hy you're traveling in the first place.</p><p></p><p>LANATA: When you plan =
a trip, it's important to define the purpose of your trip and what matters =
most to you.</p><p></p><p>EDELMAN: That's Nishann. She says, defining your =
trip is all about planning and prioritizing. Is the trip's main purpose, ex=
ploration, learning, family connection, relaxation, or something else entir=
ely?</p><p></p><p>LANATA: You can start to apply a proper budget to those d=
ifferent items based off of, I know what the purpose of this time is, this =
vacation, this trip, this exploration, and then being able to adjust from t=
here. When you have that purpose, it really helps clear up your priorities =
